              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:φραγμός&lt;SDBG:φραγμός:000000&gt;}[a] ‘fence,’ {D:7.59}) that which serves as a means of separation in interpersonal relations</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>that which separates</Gloss>
                <Gloss>that which isolates</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages, however, it may be necessary to indicate what or who is separated, and therefore one may need to translate this phrase in {S:04900201400032} as ‘… that separates Jews from Gentiles.’</Comments>
